      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:54:1",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/54/75",
      "text": [
        " «يُومِئُ بِرَأْسِهِ وَ يُشِيرُ بِيَدِهِ وَ يُسَبِّحُ وَ اَلْمَرْأَةُ إِذَا أَرَادَتِ اَلْحَاجَةَ وَ هِيَ تُصَلِّي تُصَفِّقُ بِيَدَيْهَا."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1075 - Al-Halabi asked him about a man who wishes to attend to a need while praying.\nImam (as) said: \"He should gesture with his head, signal with his hand, and glorify (SubhanAllah (swt)). As for a woman, when She wants to attend to a need while praying, She should clap her hands”."
        ]
      }
